\f2\b\fs40 \cf0 Box Breathing (4\'964\'964\'964)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf0 What this is
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Box Breathing is a structured breathing technique that uses four equal phases\'97inhale, hold, exhale, hold\'97to create balance in the nervous system. It\'92s called \'93box\'94 breathing because each breath traces the four equal sides of a square.\
This pattern is commonly used by first responders, athletes, and people in high-pressure environments because it reliably brings the body out of fight-or-flight and back into a state of steadiness.\
What matters here isn\'92t deep breathing or relaxation.\uc0\u8232 What matters is 
\f1\b pattern
\f0\b0 .\
Your nervous system responds to rhythm. When the rhythm becomes even and predictable, your body gets the signal: 
\f3\i I\'92m safe enough to settle.
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Why this works
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 When stress is high, breathing becomes shallow and uneven. That keeps the body in alert mode.\
Box Breathing does the opposite.\uc0\u8232 The equal timing:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
slows your heart rate\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
reduces stress arousal\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
activates the parasympathetic nervous system\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0
\cf0 You\'92re not forcing calm.\uc0\u8232 You\'92re creating the conditions where calm can happen.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 The practice
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Find a comfortable position. You can sit upright or rest back\'97whatever allows your body to feel supported. Let your shoulders drop. Let your jaw soften.\
You don\'92t need to change how you feel before you begin.\
This breath will meet you exactly where you are.\
We\'92ll breathe in four equal phases:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Inhale for 
\f1\b 4
\f0\b0 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Hold for 
\f1\b 4
\f0\b0 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Exhale for 
\f1\b 4
\f0\b0 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Hold for 
\f1\b 4
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0
\cf0 If four seconds feels too long, shorten it to three.\uc0\u8232 If holding your breath feels uncomfortable today, soften the holds.\u8232 There is no failing this practice.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Let\'92s begin.\
Inhale through your nose for 
\f1\b 1\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Hold gently for 
\f1\b 1\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Exhale slowly through your mouth for 
\f1\b 1\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Pause, empty, for 
\f1\b 1\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \
Again.\
Inhale 
\f1\b 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Hold 
\f1\b 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Exhale 
\f1\b 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 Pause 
\f1\b 2\'85 3\'85 4
\f0\b0 \
As you continue, imagine tracing the four sides of a square\'97each side even, steady, contained.\
Stay with this rhythm for 
\f1\b 6 cycles
\f0\b0 , or about 
\f1\b 3 minutes
\f0\b0 .\uc0\u8232 If it feels supportive, you can continue up to 
\f1\b 5 minutes
\f0\b0 .\
If your mind wanders, gently return to the count.\uc0\u8232 The pattern is doing the work.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Closing reflection
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Now let the structure fade.\uc0\u8232 Allow your breath to return to its natural rhythm.\
Notice what\'92s different.\
Maybe your chest feels softer.\uc0\u8232 Maybe your thoughts feel less sharp.\u8232 Maybe there\'92s simply more space than before.\
You didn\'92t remove the pressure in your life.\uc0\u8232 You changed your relationship to it.\
This is what regulation feels like.\
Box Breathing is a tool you can return to anytime\'97before a hard conversation, when your thoughts start spiraling, or when your body feels tense without a clear reason.\
Four sides.\uc0\u8232 One steady rhythm.\u8232 A way back to yourself.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
