\cf12 \cb2 Phoenix Omega V4 is a **prose-first book authoring system**.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 It does NOT assemble books by concatenating sections.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 It authors chapters as continuous prose.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## Chapter Authority\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 A chapter is a single, flowing prose body.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Sections are NOT output units.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 Sections are semantic roles used to fill prose slots.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 If a chapter cannot be read aloud without seams, it is invalid.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## Chapter Arc (Non-Negotiable)\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Every chapter must contain, in order:\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 1. Orientation\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 2. Pattern Exposure\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 3. Meaning / Reframe\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 4. Integration\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 5. Optional Practice (at most one)\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Missing any element = generation aborts.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## Exercises (Single Source of Truth)\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 EXERCISE IS NOT A SECTION.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Exercises may only exist in:\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 chapter.exercise_plan\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Rules:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Max 1 exercise per chapter\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Exercises are embedded in prose\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Exercises are introduced narratively\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Exercises are never standalone blocks\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 If section.type == EXERCISE \uc0\u8594  INVALID PLAN.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## Duplication Rules\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Verbatim prose duplication is forbidden:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Within a chapter\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Across chapters\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Recognition is allowed.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 Repetition is not.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## Validation Philosophy\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Phoenix fails hard.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Invalid prose does not warn.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 Invalid prose aborts generation.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 If output exists, it has already passed all contracts.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## Non-Goals\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 Phoenix does not:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Optimize for speed over quality\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Allow \'93mostly correct\'94 output\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 - Defer authorial concerns to post-processing\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ## In Case of Confusion\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 If you are unsure how to implement something:\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 1. Preserve prose authority\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 2. Preserve chapter arc\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf12 \cb2 3. Preserve single exercise rule\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 When in doubt, abort.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \
\
\cf12 \cb2 End of document.\cf0 \cb1 \
\
