\f0\b0\fs32 \cf0 Your body is holding all of this right now. You're allowed to feel exactly this exhausted. You don't have to perform having energy you don't have. And right here, in this moment, there's something that can help. Not by making everything disappear, but by giving your nervous system a way to remember it can settle. I want to show you a breathing practice. It's simple\'97your body already knows how to do this. We're just going to work with it intentionally. Let's practice together.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 This is Box Breathing. It's called that because each round has four equal sides: inhale, hold, exhale, hold. Four counts each. Like tracing the edges of a square.\
Before we begin, just get comfortable. If you're sitting, let your feet touch the floor. If you're lying down, let your shoulders soften. Let your jaw unclench. You don't have to force calm. We're not chasing calm. We're just giving your body a structure it can trust.\
If it feels okay, place one hand on your belly, or one hand on your chest\'97wherever you can feel your breath more clearly. If that feels weird, skip it. Just notice that you're breathing.\
We're going to do six rounds.\
Here we go.\
Round one.\
Inhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\uc0\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Exhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\
Round two.\
Inhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\uc0\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Exhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\
Round three.\
Inhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\uc0\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Exhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\
