Round five.\
Inhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\uc0\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Exhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\
Round six.\
Inhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\uc0\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Exhale\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\u8232 Hold\'85 2\'85 3\'85 4.\
Now let the counting go.\
Let your breathing return to its natural rhythm.\
And just notice what changed.\
Not \'93did the anxiety disappear.\'94 Not \'93am I fixed.\'94 Just this:\
Is there even one percent more space inside your chest?\uc0\u8232 One percent less pressure behind your eyes?\u8232 One percent more room in your belly?\
That is the point.\
Because your nervous system doesn't need a lecture. It needs repetition of safety. It needs little proof moments that say: \'93I can come down.\'94\
And every time you do this, you're teaching your body something important.\
You're teaching it: \'93I can be here and still breathe.\'94\uc0\u8232 \'93I can feel this and still come back.\'94\u8232 \'93I can be stressed and still have a way through.\'94\
